<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <title>The First 30 Days — A Quiet Plan for Early Sobriety</title>
  <style>
    /* ─── PAGE GEOMETRY ─────────────────────────────────────────────── */
    @page {
      size: 6in 9in;
      margin: 0;
    }
    @page :first {
      margin: 0;
    }

    /* ─── RESET ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
    * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
    html, body { -webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; print-color-adjust: exact; }

    :root {
      --bg:        #07080f;
      --bg-soft:   #0f1420;
      --ink:       #ebe7df;
      --ink-soft:  #aea48f;
      --ink-mute:  #6a6354;
      --sage:      #9be7c5;
      --sage-deep: #43c486;
      --amber:     #f0b860;
      --amber-deep:#c08838;
      --rust:      #d97a55;
      --rule:      rgba(155,231,197,0.18);
      --rule-soft: rgba(235,231,223,0.10);
    }

    html { font-size: 10pt; }

    body {
      font-family: "Iowan Old Style", "Palatino Linotype", "Georgia", serif;
      color: var(--ink);
      background: var(--bg);
      line-height: 1.35;
      font-feature-settings: "kern" 1, "liga" 1;
    }

    .sans {
      font-family: "Inter", "Helvetica Neue", system-ui, sans-serif;
      letter-spacing: 0.01em;
    }

    .display {
      font-family: "Fraunces", "Iowan Old Style", "Georgia", serif;
      font-weight: 700;
      letter-spacing: -0.02em;
      line-height: 1.05;
    }

    /* ─── PAGE FRAME ─────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
    .page {
      width: 6in;
      height: 9in;
      position: relative;
      page-break-after: always;
      overflow: hidden;
      background: var(--bg);
    }
    .page::after {
      content: "";
      position: absolute;
      left: 0.6in;
      right: 0.6in;
      bottom: 0.35in;
      height: 1px;
      background: var(--rule-soft);
    }
    .page-content {
      padding: 0.55in 0.5in 0.5in 0.5in;
      height: 100%;
      position: relative;
    }
    .folio {
      position: absolute;
      bottom: 0.22in;
      left: 0;
      right: 0;
      text-align: center;
      font-family: "Inter", sans-serif;
      font-size: 8pt;
      color: var(--ink-mute);
      letter-spacing: 0.15em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
    }

    /* ─── COVER ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
    .cover {
      position: relative;
      width: 6in;
      height: 9in;
      page-break-after: always;
      overflow: hidden;
      background: #000;
    }
    .cover img {
      position: absolute;
      inset: 0;
      width: 100%;
      height: 100%;
      object-fit: cover;
    }
    .cover::before {
      content: "";
      position: absolute;
      inset: 0;
      background: linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(7,8,15,0.10) 0%, rgba(7,8,15,0.55) 60%, rgba(7,8,15,0.95) 100%);
      z-index: 1;
    }
    .cover-content {
      position: absolute;
      inset: 0;
      z-index: 2;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      justify-content: flex-end;
      padding: 0.6in;
      color: var(--ink);
    }
    .cover-eyebrow {
      font-family: "Inter", sans-serif;
      font-size: 9pt;
      letter-spacing: 0.3em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--amber);
      margin-bottom: 14pt;
    }
    .cover-title {
      font-family: "Fraunces", "Iowan Old Style", serif;
      font-size: 38pt;
      font-weight: 700;
      line-height: 1.0;
      letter-spacing: -0.025em;
      color: #fff;
      margin-bottom: 14pt;
    }
    .cover-subtitle {
      font-family: "Iowan Old Style", serif;
      font-style: italic;
      font-size: 13pt;
      color: rgba(235,231,223,0.85);
      line-height: 1.4;
      margin-bottom: 28pt;
      max-width: 4.6in;
    }
    .cover-by {
      font-family: "Inter", sans-serif;
      font-size: 9pt;
      letter-spacing: 0.2em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: rgba(235,231,223,0.55);
    }
    .cover-by strong { color: var(--sage); font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.25em; }

    /* ─── HEADINGS ──────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
    h1, h2, h3 { font-family: "Fraunces", "Iowan Old Style", serif; }
    h1 { font-size: 24pt; line-height: 1.05; letter-spacing: -0.02em; }
    h2 { font-size: 14pt; line-height: 1.15; letter-spacing: -0.01em; margin: 8pt 0 4pt; }
    h3 { font-size: 11pt; line-height: 1.2; margin: 6pt 0 2pt; color: var(--sage); letter-spacing: 0.02em; }

    .eyebrow {
      font-family: "Inter", sans-serif;
      font-size: 8.5pt;
      letter-spacing: 0.25em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--amber);
      margin-bottom: 10pt;
      font-weight: 600;
    }

    p { margin: 0 0 5pt; }
    p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

    ul, ol { margin: 4pt 0 6pt 16pt; }
    li { margin-bottom: 2pt; }

    blockquote {
      margin: 10pt 6pt;
      padding: 10pt 14pt;
      border-left: 2px solid var(--sage);
      font-style: italic;
      color: var(--ink-soft);
      background: rgba(155,231,197,0.04);
      break-inside: avoid;
      border-radius: 0 4pt 4pt 0;
    }

    strong { color: #fff; font-weight: 600; }
    em { font-style: italic; color: var(--ink-soft); }

    a { color: var(--sage); text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--sage-deep); }

    /* ─── TITLE / OPENING PAGE ──────────────────────────────────────── */
    .opening-page {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      justify-content: space-between;
    }
    .title-block {
      margin-top: 1.2in;
    }
    .title-eyebrow {
      font-family: "Inter", sans-serif;
      font-size: 9pt;
      letter-spacing: 0.3em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--amber);
      margin-bottom: 16pt;
    }
    .title-main {
      font-family: "Fraunces", serif;
      font-size: 42pt;
      font-weight: 700;
      line-height: 0.98;
      letter-spacing: -0.03em;
      color: var(--ink);
      margin-bottom: 22pt;
    }
    .title-sub {
      font-style: italic;
      font-size: 14pt;
      line-height: 1.45;
      color: var(--ink-soft);
      max-width: 4.6in;
      margin-bottom: 30pt;
    }
    .title-credits {
      border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
      padding-top: 14pt;
      font-family: "Inter", sans-serif;
      font-size: 9pt;
      letter-spacing: 0.06em;
      color: var(--ink-mute);
    }
    .title-credits strong { color: var(--sage); letter-spacing: 0.2em; }

    /* ─── SECTION DIVIDER ───────────────────────────────────────────── */
    .divider {
      width: 100%;
      text-align: center;
      margin: 22pt 0 18pt;
      color: var(--ink-mute);
      font-family: "Inter", sans-serif;
      font-size: 8pt;
      letter-spacing: 0.4em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      position: relative;
    }
    .divider::before, .divider::after {
      content: "";
      position: absolute;
      top: 50%;
      width: 30%;
      height: 1px;
      background: var(--rule);
    }
    .divider::before { left: 0; }
    .divider::after { right: 0; }

    /* ─── CALLOUT BOX ────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
    .callout {
      margin: 12pt 0;
      padding: 12pt 14pt;
      background: rgba(240,184,96,0.08);
      border-left: 3px solid var(--amber);
      border-radius: 0 4pt 4pt 0;
      break-inside: avoid;
      page-break-inside: avoid;
    }
    .callout .label {
      font-family: "Inter", sans-serif;
      font-size: 8pt;
      letter-spacing: 0.25em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--amber);
      font-weight: 600;
      margin-bottom: 4pt;
    }
    .callout p:last-child { margin: 0; }
    .callout strong { color: var(--ink); }

    /* ─── WORKSHEET ─────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
    .worksheet {
      margin: 10pt 0;
      padding: 14pt;
      border: 1.5pt solid var(--rule);
      border-radius: 4pt;
      background: rgba(255,255,255,0.02);
      break-inside: avoid;
      page-break-inside: avoid;
    }
    .worksheet-title {
      font-family: "Inter", sans-serif;
      font-size: 9pt;
      letter-spacing: 0.25em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--sage);
      margin-bottom: 10pt;
      font-weight: 700;
    }
    .worksheet-sub {
      font-size: 9.5pt;
      font-style: italic;
      color: var(--ink-soft);
      margin-bottom: 12pt;
    }
    .field {
      margin: 8pt 0;
    }
    .field-label {
      font-family: "Inter", sans-serif;
      font-size: 8.5pt;
      letter-spacing: 0.06em;
      color: var(--ink-soft);
      margin-bottom: 4pt;
    }
    .field-line {
      border-bottom: 0.5pt solid var(--ink-mute);
      height: 14pt;
    }
    .field-line-tall {
      border-bottom: 0.5pt solid var(--ink-mute);
      min-height: 38pt;
    }
    .field-grid-2 {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: 10pt;
    }
    .field-grid-3 {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr;
      gap: 10pt;
    }
    .checklist-item {
      display: flex;
      align-items: flex-start;
      gap: 8pt;
      margin: 5pt 0;
      font-size: 10pt;
    }
    .check {
      width: 11pt;
      height: 11pt;
      border: 0.7pt solid var(--ink-mute);
      border-radius: 2pt;
      flex-shrink: 0;
      margin-top: 3pt;
    }
    .number-list {
      counter-reset: step;
      list-style: none;
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
    }
    .number-list li {
      counter-increment: step;
      display: flex;
      gap: 12pt;
      margin-bottom: 10pt;
      padding-left: 0;
    }
    .number-list li::before {
      content: counter(step);
      flex-shrink: 0;
      width: 22pt;
      height: 22pt;
      border: 1pt solid var(--amber);
      border-radius: 50%;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      font-family: "Inter", sans-serif;
      font-size: 10pt;
      font-weight: 600;
      color: var(--amber);
      margin-top: 1pt;
    }

    /* ─── PULL QUOTE ────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
    .pull-quote {
      margin: 14pt 4pt;
      padding: 14pt 12pt;
      text-align: center;
      font-family: "Fraunces", serif;
      font-style: italic;
      font-size: 14pt;
      line-height: 1.3;
      color: var(--amber);
      border-top: 1px solid var(--amber);
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--amber);
      break-inside: avoid;
      page-break-inside: avoid;
    }

    /* ─── FOOTER (CTA) ──────────────────────────────────────────────── */
    .cta-page {
      background: linear-gradient(180deg, #050810 0%, #0c1a14 100%);
    }
    .cta-page .page-content {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      justify-content: space-between;
      padding-top: 0.4in;
    }
    .cta-hero {
      text-align: center;
      margin-top: 0;
    }
    .cta-hero .eyebrow { margin-bottom: 14pt; }
    .cta-title {
      font-family: "Fraunces", serif;
      font-size: 26pt;
      font-weight: 700;
      line-height: 1.08;
      letter-spacing: -0.02em;
      color: #fff;
      margin-bottom: 14pt;
    }
    .cta-sub {
      font-size: 11pt;
      color: var(--ink-soft);
      max-width: 4.4in;
      margin: 0 auto 18pt;
      line-height: 1.5;
    }
    .cta-features {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: 10pt;
      margin: 14pt 0;
    }
    .cta-feat {
      padding: 9pt 10pt;
      border: 1pt solid var(--rule);
      border-radius: 4pt;
      background: rgba(155,231,197,0.03);
      text-align: left;
    }
    .cta-feat-emoji {
      font-size: 14pt;
      margin-bottom: 2pt;
    }
    .cta-feat-title {
      font-family: "Inter", sans-serif;
      font-size: 9pt;
      letter-spacing: 0.05em;
      color: var(--sage);
      font-weight: 600;
      margin-bottom: 2pt;
    }
    .cta-feat-body {
      font-size: 8.5pt;
      color: var(--ink-soft);
      line-height: 1.4;
    }
    .cta-button {
      display: inline-block;
      padding: 12pt 28pt;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--sage) 0%, var(--sage-deep) 100%);
      color: #07080f;
      border-radius: 6pt;
      font-family: "Inter", sans-serif;
      font-size: 11pt;
      font-weight: 700;
      letter-spacing: 0.04em;
      text-decoration: none;
      border-bottom: none;
      margin: 6pt 0;
    }
    .cta-url {
      font-family: "Inter", sans-serif;
      font-size: 9.5pt;
      color: var(--ink-mute);
      margin-top: 4pt;
    }
    .cta-url code {
      background: rgba(155,231,197,0.08);
      color: var(--sage);
      padding: 2pt 6pt;
      border-radius: 3pt;
      font-family: "JetBrains Mono", "Courier New", monospace;
      font-size: 9pt;
    }

    /* ─── EMAIL OPT-IN ─────────────────────────────────────────────── */
    .optin {
      margin: 16pt auto 0;
      max-width: 4.5in;
      padding: 16pt 18pt;
      background: rgba(255,255,255,0.03);
      border: 1pt solid var(--rule);
      border-radius: 6pt;
      text-align: left;
    }
    .optin-eyebrow {
      font-family: "Inter", sans-serif;
      font-size: 8pt;
      letter-spacing: 0.3em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--amber);
      font-weight: 700;
      margin-bottom: 4pt;
    }
    .optin-title {
      font-family: "Fraunces", serif;
      font-size: 14pt;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: #fff;
      margin-bottom: 6pt;
    }
    .optin-body {
      font-size: 9.5pt;
      color: var(--ink-soft);
      line-height: 1.55;
      margin-bottom: 10pt;
    }
    .optin-form {
      display: flex;
      gap: 6pt;
    }
    .optin-input {
      flex: 1;
      padding: 8pt 12pt;
      background: rgba(255,255,255,0.05);
      border: 0.7pt solid var(--ink-mute);
      border-radius: 4pt;
      color: var(--ink);
      font-family: "Inter", sans-serif;
      font-size: 9.5pt;
    }
    .optin-btn {
      padding: 8pt 16pt;
      background: var(--amber);
      color: #07080f;
      border: 0;
      border-radius: 4pt;
      font-family: "Inter", sans-serif;
      font-size: 9pt;
      font-weight: 700;
      letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    }
    .optin-note {
      font-size: 8pt;
      color: var(--ink-mute);
      font-style: italic;
      margin-top: 6pt;
    }

    .cta-footer {
      text-align: center;
      border-top: 1pt solid var(--rule-soft);
      padding-top: 14pt;
      font-family: "Inter", sans-serif;
      font-size: 8pt;
      letter-spacing: 0.1em;
      color: var(--ink-mute);
    }

    /* ─── TOC ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
    .toc-item {
      display: flex;
      justify-content: space-between;
      align-items: baseline;
      padding: 6pt 0;
      border-bottom: 0.5pt solid var(--rule-soft);
      font-size: 10pt;
    }
    .toc-item:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
    .toc-num {
      font-family: "Inter", sans-serif;
      font-size: 8pt;
      color: var(--ink-mute);
      letter-spacing: 0.1em;
      width: 28pt;
      flex-shrink: 0;
    }
    .toc-title {
      flex: 1;
      color: var(--ink);
    }
    .toc-page {
      font-family: "Inter", sans-serif;
      font-size: 9pt;
      color: var(--amber);
      letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    }

    /* ─── DO/WHEN LISTS ─────────────────────────────────────────────── */
    .two-col {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: 14pt;
      margin: 10pt 0;
    }
    .col-block {
      padding: 12pt;
      border-radius: 4pt;
    }
    .col-block.do {
      background: rgba(155,231,197,0.05);
      border-left: 2pt solid var(--sage);
    }
    .col-block.dont {
      background: rgba(217,122,85,0.05);
      border-left: 2pt solid var(--rust);
    }
    .col-label {
      font-family: "Inter", sans-serif;
      font-size: 8pt;
      letter-spacing: 0.25em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      font-weight: 700;
      margin-bottom: 6pt;
    }
    .col-block.do .col-label { color: var(--sage); }
    .col-block.dont .col-label { color: var(--rust); }
    .col-block ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 16pt; font-size: 9.5pt; }
    .col-block li { margin-bottom: 4pt; }

    /* ─── TABLE / GRID FOR LISTS ────────────────────────────────────── */
    .day-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 60pt 1fr;
      gap: 12pt;
      margin: 8pt 0;
    }
    .day-num {
      font-family: "Fraunces", serif;
      font-size: 26pt;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: var(--amber);
      line-height: 1;
    }
    .day-content h3 { margin: 0 0 4pt; color: var(--ink); font-size: 12pt; }

    /* ─── CRISIS BOX ────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
    .crisis {
      margin: 12pt 0;
      padding: 12pt 14pt;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(217,122,85,0.10) 0%, rgba(217,122,85,0.04) 100%);
      border: 1.5pt solid var(--rust);
      border-radius: 4pt;
      break-inside: avoid;
      page-break-inside: avoid;
    }
    .crisis-title {
      font-family: "Inter", sans-serif;
      font-size: 10pt;
      letter-spacing: 0.3em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--rust);
      font-weight: 700;
      margin-bottom: 8pt;
    }
    .crisis p { margin-bottom: 4pt; }
    .crisis strong { color: #fff; }

    /* ─── BACK COVER ────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
    .back-cover {
      background: linear-gradient(180deg, #050810 0%, #07080f 100%);
      padding: 0.9in 0.6in 0.7in 0.6in;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      justify-content: space-around;
      text-align: center;
    }
    .back-cover .brand {
      font-family: "Fraunces", serif;
      font-size: 22pt;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: var(--ink);
      letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    }
    .back-cover .brand-sub {
      font-family: "Inter", sans-serif;
      font-size: 8pt;
      letter-spacing: 0.3em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--sage);
      margin-top: 4pt;
    }
    .back-cover .mantra {
      font-family: "Fraunces", serif;
      font-style: italic;
      font-size: 13pt;
      line-height: 1.5;
      color: var(--ink-soft);
      margin: 0 auto;
      max-width: 4.4in;
    }
    .back-cover .legal {
      font-family: "Inter", sans-serif;
      font-size: 7.5pt;
      color: var(--ink-mute);
      line-height: 1.5;
    }

  </style>
</head>
<body>

<!-- ─────────────────────── PAGE 1: COVER ─────────────────────── -->
<div class="cover">
  <img src="../cover-bg.png" alt="A candle burning softly in predawn darkness" />
  <div class="cover-content">
    <div class="cover-eyebrow">A BreakFree Guide · Volume One</div>
    <h1 class="cover-title">The First<br/>30 Days</h1>
    <div class="cover-subtitle">A quiet plan for early sobriety — written by people who've been where you are.</div>
    <div class="cover-by">Published by <strong>BreakFree</strong></div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ─────────────────────── PAGE 2: TITLE / OPENING ─────────────────────── -->
<div class="page">
  <div class="page-content opening-page">
    <div class="title-block">
      <div class="title-eyebrow">BreakFree · Volume One</div>
      <div class="title-main display">The First 30 Days</div>
      <div class="title-sub">A quiet plan for early sobriety — written by people who've been where you are, for the person standing at the start of the road.</div>
      <div class="title-credits">
        <strong>FIRST EDITION · 2026</strong><br/>
        Published by BreakFree · breakfree.app<br/>
        A companion to the BreakFree recovery app
      </div>
    </div>

    <div>
      <div class="divider">A note before we start</div>
      <p style="margin-top:14pt">If you're reading this on day one — or close to it — you don't need a pep talk. You need a plan. So this isn't a self-help book. It's a workbook, a notebook, and a series of honest letters from people who got through the first thirty days and came out the other side.</p>
      <p>You don't have to do everything here. You don't even have to do most of it. Pick the parts that sound useful, ignore the rest, and come back to it when you need to.</p>
      <blockquote>The most important thing in the first thirty days is that there is a thirty-first day. — Sage, BreakFree's AI coach</blockquote>
    </div>

    <div class="folio">I · A note before we start</div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ─────────────────────── PAGE 3: TABLE OF CONTENTS ─────────────────────── -->
<div class="page">
  <div class="page-content">
    <div class="eyebrow">Contents</div>
    <h1 class="display" style="font-size:28pt; margin-bottom:18pt">What's inside</h1>

    <div class="toc-item"><span class="toc-num">I</span><span class="toc-title">A note before we start</span><span class="toc-page">2</span></div>
    <div class="toc-item"><span class="toc-num">II</span><span class="toc-title">Before day one — the practical prep</span><span class="toc-page">4</span></div>
    <div class="toc-item"><span class="toc-num">III</span><span class="toc-title">Days 1–7 — the first week</span><span class="toc-page">6</span></div>
    <div class="toc-item"><span class="toc-num">IV</span><span class="toc-title">Worksheet · My first seven days</span><span class="toc-page">8</span></div>
    <div class="toc-item"><span class="toc-num">V</span><span class="toc-title">Days 8–14 — the wave</span><span class="toc-page">10</span></div>
    <div class="toc-item"><span class="toc-num">VI</span><span class="toc-title">Days 15–21 — the people</span><span class="toc-page">13</span></div>
    <div class="toc-item"><span class="toc-num">VII</span><span class="toc-title">Days 22–30 — the foundation</span><span class="toc-page">15</span></div>
    <div class="toc-item"><span class="toc-num">VIII</span><span class="toc-title">When the urge hits — your toolkit</span><span class="toc-page">21</span></div>
    <div class="toc-item"><span class="toc-num">IX</span><span class="toc-title">If you slip — what to do next</span><span class="toc-page">23</span></div>
    <div class="toc-item"><span class="toc-num">X</span><span class="toc-title">After day 30 — what comes next</span><span class="toc-page">24</span></div>
    <div class="toc-item"><span class="toc-num">XI</span><span class="toc-title">About BreakFree & how to get it</span><span class="toc-page">25</span></div>

    <div class="callout" style="margin-top:20pt">
      <div class="label">About the worksheets</div>
      <p>The five worksheets inside this guide are designed to be filled in by hand, in a notebook or printed out. They don't grade you. They're a record of what you're noticing. Some of the questions don't have answers yet — that's the point. Put a date on each one. Come back to them on day 30.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="folio">Contents</div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ─────────────────────── PAGE 4: BEFORE DAY ONE ─────────────────────── -->
<div class="page">
  <div class="page-content">
    <div class="eyebrow">Chapter II</div>
    <h1 class="display">Before day one</h1>
    <h2 class="display">The practical prep</h2>

    <p>If you can, do these in the 24 hours before you stop. You won't always get this window, and that's fine — but if you do, it removes a layer of friction that nobody tells you about.</p>

    <h3>Remove the obvious triggers</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Anything in your house you'd use. Pour it out, throw it out, give it away. Not "hide it" — remove it.</li>
      <li>Delete the apps, unfollow the accounts, block the numbers. Don't give yourself a 2am decision to make.</li>
      <li>Tell one person. Not your whole list. One person who will not freak out. Just: "I'm starting today."</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Add the obvious supports</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Stock easy food. Things you can eat at 2am if you need to. Bread, peanut butter, fruit, cereal. Nothing fancy.</li>
      <li>Water. More than you think. The first three days feel like dehydration even when they aren't.</li>
      <li>A thing you can do with your hands for ten minutes — a podcast, a walk, a shower, a recipe, a text to a friend.</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="callout">
      <div class="label">The single most important prep</div>
      <p>Plan your first 24 hours in detail. Not "I'll be fine." Actual: when you wake up, what you eat, who you text, where you go, what you do at 3pm, 5pm, 9pm. The people who make it through day one had a plan. The people who don't, didn't.</p>
    </div>

    <h3 style="break-before: page;">Decide on your morning ritual</h3>
    <p>You don't need to meditate for an hour. You need three things you'll do before you leave the house or start your day. Suggested starting set:</p>

    <div class="two-col">
      <div class="col-block do">
        <div class="col-label">Do this</div>
        <ul>
          <li>Glass of water before coffee</li>
          <li>One minute of light (curtain open or step outside)</li>
          <li>Write one sentence about how you feel</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="col-block dont">
        <div class="col-label">Skip this</div>
        <ul>
          <li>Checking your phone first thing</li>
          <li>Counting the day in your head</li>
          <li>Forcing yourself to "feel" like a person in recovery</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="folio">II · Before day one</div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ─────────────────────── PAGE 5: SAME (continued) ─────────────────────── -->
<div class="page">
  <div class="page-content">
    <div class="eyebrow">Chapter II (continued)</div>
    <h1 class="display" style="font-size:24pt">What to expect in the first 72 hours</h1>

    <p>You may have read online that the first three days are the hardest. They're not wrong. Here's what actually happens, so it's not a surprise:</p>

    <div class="day-grid">
      <div class="day-num">01</div>
      <div class="day-content">
        <h3>Your body is recalibrating</h3>
        <p>Tremors, sweating, nausea, headache, restlessness, intense cravings, disturbed sleep. All normal. All temporary. None of them mean you're broken. If symptoms get severe, that's not weakness — call a doctor. There's no award for white-knuckling it through something dangerous.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="day-grid">
      <div class="day-num">02</div>
      <div class="day-content">
        <h3>Your emotions are loud</h3>
        <p>Whatever you've been numbing comes up. Boredom, anger, sadness, restlessness. These are not signs you're doing it wrong — they're signs you're doing it right and feeling things for the first time. Ride them. Don't argue with them.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="day-grid">
      <div class="day-num">03</div>
      <div class="day-content">
        <h3>The voice gets louder before it gets quieter</h3>
        <p>Around day two or three, the craving voice often peaks. It tells you that one wouldn't matter, that you can control it, that you deserve it. The voice is a liar. You already know it's a liar. You just need to outlast it for the next ten minutes. One ten minutes at a time.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="pull-quote">The craving is doing what it does. You don't have to do what it does.</div>

    <h3>The simplest coping toolkit for the first 72 hours</h3>
    <p>Pick one or two. Don't try all of them.</p>

    <div class="two-col">
      <div class="col-block do">
        <div class="col-label">Do</div>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>4-7-8 breath:</strong> 4 in, hold 7, out 8. Four rounds.</li>
          <li><strong>Cold water:</strong> on face and wrists.</li>
          <li><strong>Walk one block:</strong> just one, then back.</li>
          <li><strong>Call one person:</strong> voice, not text.</li>
          <li><strong>Eat something:</strong> anything.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="col-block dont">
        <div class="col-label">Skip</div>
        <ul>
          <li>Trying to be "productive" through it</li>
          <li>Big life decisions at 2am</li>
          <li>Scrolling your phone for two hours</li>
          <li>Being alone with it and calling it "self-care"</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="folio">II · Before day one</div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ─────────────────────── PAGE 6: DAYS 1-7 ─────────────────────── -->
<div class="page">
  <div class="page-content">
    <div class="eyebrow">Chapter III</div>
    <h1 class="display">Days 1–7</h1>
    <h2 class="display">The first week</h2>

    <p>The first week is mostly a holding pattern. You're not building anything. You're not "getting better." You're just not using. That's the work. Here's what each day looks roughly like:</p>

    <h3>The shape of a first-week day</h3>
    <ol class="number-list">
      <li><span><strong>Morning:</strong> water, light, breakfast. Your morning ritual. Don't decide anything important before 10am.</span></li>
      <li><span><strong>Midday:</strong> one task. Not seven. One thing that takes an hour and isn't drinking, using, or scrolling. Walk, clean a drawer, answer an email.</span></li>
      <li><span><strong>Afternoon:</strong> the voice gets loud. This is the wave. Use one tool from the toolkit. Eat. Move your body. Talk to a human.</span></li>
      <li><span><strong>Evening:</strong> food, company if you can get it, one show or book. Phone in another room by 10pm.</span></li>
    </ol>

    <div class="callout">
      <div class="label">A note on the "voice"</div>
      <p>You'll start to notice a particular voice in your head that wasn't there before. It's loudest in the afternoon, around 3-5pm. It says things like "you're missing out," "one wouldn't hurt," "you've earned it," "you can control it this time." This voice is not you. It's a pattern your brain runs when it expects the thing it's missing. You don't have to argue with it. You just have to outlast it. Ten minutes at a time.</p>
    </div>

    <h3>What to say to people who ask</h3>
    <p>"I'm taking a break." "I'm off it for a while." "Doctor's orders." You don't owe anyone the long version. The longer the version, the more they argue with. The shorter the version, the more they shrug and move on. Most people will forget in three days. Let them.</p>

    <h3 style="break-before: page;">What to do at 3am</h3>
    <p>It will come. You'll wake up at 3am on night three or four. Here's the plan: water, bathroom, three deep breaths, name one thing you can see, go back to bed. Do not pick up your phone. Do not check if you "feel" different. Do not negotiate. Just water, breath, back to bed.</p>

    <div class="folio">III · Days 1–7</div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ─────────────────────── PAGE 7: DAYS 1-7 (continued) ─────────────────────── -->
<div class="page">
  <div class="page-content">
    <div class="eyebrow">Chapter III (continued)</div>
    <h1 class="display" style="font-size:22pt; break-before: page;">What you'll notice this week</h1>

    <p>These are not warnings or predictions. Just things people often report, so they don't surprise you when they happen.</p>

    <div class="day-grid">
      <div class="day-num">D2</div>
      <div class="day-content"><h3>Sleep gets weird before it gets better</h3><p>Vivid dreams. Trouble falling asleep. Waking up at 3am. By day five or six, sleep usually starts to settle. If it doesn't, that's a real thing — talk to someone.</p></div>
    </div>
    <div class="day-grid">
      <div class="day-num">D3</div>
      <div class="day-content"><h3>You'll feel both proud and terrified at the same time</h3><p>This is normal. The pride and the terror are both real. Don't let one cancel out the other.</p></div>
    </div>
    <div class="day-grid">
      <div class="day-num">D4</div>
      <div class="day-content"><h3>You'll start to notice things you were numbing</h3><p>An old feeling. An old conversation. A song. Let them come. They were always there. They're just louder now because you're not drowning them.</p></div>
    </div>
    <div class="day-grid">
      <div class="day-num">D5</div>
      <div class="day-content"><h3>You might cry at a commercial</h3><p>This is also normal. Your emotional range is coming back online. It's uncomfortable. It's also a sign you're healing.</p></div>
    </div>
    <div class="day-grid">
      <div class="day-num">D6</div>
      <div class="day-content"><h3>The "I can do this forever" feeling</h3><p>Don't trust it. The day you feel most confident is often the day the craving catches you off-guard. Stay humble. Stay in the toolkit.</p></div>
    </div>
    <div class="day-grid">
      <div class="day-num">D7</div>
      <div class="day-content"><h3>Seven days</h3><p>One week. Not a victory lap. Not proof you've beaten anything. Just proof that the wave comes and goes. That's all you need to keep going.</p></div>
    </div>

    <div class="pull-quote">The wave comes. You ride it. The wave goes. You're still here.</div>

    <div class="folio">III · Days 1–7</div>
  </div>
</div>

